OL,3,CWhen do the clocks change and why does
OL,4,Cit happen?
OL,6,FBST ` or daylight saving time (DST) `
OL,7,Flasts until the final Sunday in
OL,8,FOctober, when the clocks go back an
OL,9,Fhour.
OL,11,FDoes that mean longer days?
OL,13,FEarly risers will notice darker
OL,14,Fmornings immediately after the March
OL,15,Fchange, while evenings will be lighter
OL,16,Fas the sun sets later.
OL,18,FAs sunrise and sunset times continue
OL,19,Fto extend, parts of the UK will see
OL,20,Falmost 19 hours of daylight by the
OL,21,Fsummer solstice on June 21.
