OL,3,CWhen do the clocks change and why does
OL,4,Cit happen?
OL,6,FAre there any downsides?
OL,8,FDr Kelu said: "The circadian clock
OL,9,Fregulates our physiology and
OL,10,Fmetabolism, and we know that extreme
OL,11,Fcases such as shift working, causing
OL,12,Fcircadian misalignment, will lead to
OL,13,Fincreased risk in metabolic disorders
OL,14,Fsuch as obesity and diabetes.
OL,16,F"We believe that even for daylight
OL,17,Fsavings time, the changing of the
OL,18,Fclock would be affecting health in
OL,19,Fsome sense.
